<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-14T18:56:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-14T18:56:00-05:00" n="1472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816 48/12</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-14T18:00:00-05:56">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>All night downpour drove home anew to thousands who slept in the open the
                            real need for shelter, no doubt if marines or warships have extra tents
                            Department will rush same here. Three earthquakes of unusual severity
                            during night rendered situation more disagreeable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>